,"ref":"1Sam.8.1","text":"And it came to pass, when Samuel was old, that he made his sons judges over Israel.","year":-1112},{"id":"recJMs8atgX4chBgd","ref":"1Sam.8.2","text":"Now the name of his firstborn was Joel; and the name of his second, Abiah: they were judges in Beersheba.","year":-1112},{"id":"recZvsYUl9nUpWHZ2","ref":"1Sam.8.3","text":"And his sons walked not in his ways, but turned aside after lucre, and took bribes, and perverted judgment.","year":-1112},{"id":"reckTib0bc9tEeLP5","ref":"1Sam.8.4","text":"Then all the elders of Israel gathered themselves together, and came to Samuel unto Ramah,","year":-1112},{"id":"recYF3pUZ5UOs02d4","ref":"1Sam.8.5","text":"And said unto him, Behold, thou art old, and thy sons walk not in thy ways: now make us a king to judge us like all the nations.","year":-1112},{"id":"recbs85UQ9I7p1lPH","ref":"1Sam.8.6","text":"But the thing displeased Samuel, when they said, Give us a king to judge us. And Samuel prayed unto the LORD.","year":-1112},{"id":"recJCFtrHFL8XAiky","ref":"1Sam.8.7","text":"And the LORD said unto Samuel, Hearken unto the voice of the people in all that they say unto thee: for they have not rejected thee, but they have rejected me, that I should not reign over them.","year":-1112},{"id":"recFmbKeIEhhQkPc9","ref":"1Sam.8.8","text":"According to all the works which they have done since the day that I brought them up out of Egypt even unto this day, wherewith they have forsaken me, and served other gods, so do they also unto thee.","year":-1112}]}
